The paper deals with the problem of recovering a sparse signal from noisy linear measurements, which is a common problem in signal processing and machine learning. The use of the LASSO algorithm for this purpose suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Signal Processing (cs.SP). The consideration of an imperfect measurement matrix and the analysis of the limiting behavior of the mean squared error and the probability of support recovery suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) or Systems and Control (cs.SI).
